# Use Cases - {{PRIMARY_WORKFLOW}} Platform

This document describes the 3 main use cases for a {{PRIMARY_WORKFLOW}} Platform. Each use case covers a distinct interaction pattern: a happy-path verification flow, a complex multi-step process, and a security/compliance-critical audit trail review.

## Selection Criteria

| Criterion | UC-1 | UC-2 | UC-3 |
|-----------|------|------|------|
| Interaction type | Happy path | Complex multi-step | Security/compliance |
| Primary actor | End User | End User + System | Compliance Officer |
| System complexity | Low | High | Medium |
| Regulatory impact | Medium | High | Critical |
| Frequency | High (daily) | Medium (onboarding) | Low (audit cycle) |

---

## UC-1: User {{PRIMARY_WORKFLOW}} Verification

### Description

A registered end user initiates a standard {{PRIMARY_WORKFLOW}} verification session. The system captures the user's {{VERIFICATION_DATA}}, performs {{PRIMARY_VERIFICATION_METHOD}} to confirm a {{VERIFICATION_CRITERIA}} is present, matches the captured {{SENSITIVE_DATA_TYPE}} against the stored reference template, and returns a verification result. This is the most frequent interaction and represents the happy-path flow for returning users.

### Actors

- **Primary:** End User (registered individual requesting verification)
- **Secondary:** Verification Engine (backend service performing {{VERIFICATION_TYPE}} matching)

### Preconditions

- The user has a registered account with a stored {{SENSITIVE_DATA_TYPE}} reference template
- The user's device has a functioning {{VERIFICATION_DEVICE}}
- The verification service is available and operational

### Postconditions

- The system records the verification attempt with timestamp and result
- On success, the user gains access to the protected resource
- On failure, the user receives actionable feedback

### Diagram

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    classDef actor fill:#d4edda,stroke:#28a745,color:#000
    classDef system fill:#cce5ff,stroke:#0d6efd,color:#000
    classDef decision fill:#fff3cd,stroke:#ffc107,color:#000
    classDef terminal fill:#e2e3e5,stroke:#6c757d,color:#000

    Start([User opens verification screen]):::actor
    Capture[System activates {{VERIFICATION_DEVICE}} and captures {{VERIFICATION_DATA}}]:::system
    Liveness{{{PRIMARY_VERIFICATION_METHOD}} passed?}:::decision
    Extract[System extracts {{VERIFICATION_TYPE}} features]:::system
    Match{{{VERIFICATION_TYPE}} match score above threshold?}:::decision
    LogSuccess[System logs successful verification]:::system
    GrantAccess([Access granted to protected resource]):::terminal
    LivenessFail[System displays {{PRIMARY_VERIFICATION_METHOD}} failure message]:::system
    MatchFail[System displays match failure message]:::system
    RetryPrompt([User prompted to retry or contact support]):::terminal

    subgraph VerificationEngine["System Boundary: Verification Engine"]
        Capture --> Liveness
        Liveness -->|Yes| Extract
        Extract --> Match
        Liveness -->|No| LivenessFail
        Match -->|Yes| LogSuccess
        Match -->|No| MatchFail
    end

    Start --> Capture
    LogSuccess --> GrantAccess
    LivenessFail --> RetryPrompt
    MatchFail --> RetryPrompt
```

---

## UC-2: Multi-Step Document + {{PRIMARY_WORKFLOW}} Verification

### Description

A new user completes a full onboarding verification that combines document verification with {{VERIFICATION_TYPE}} enrollment. The process requires the user to scan an identity document ({{DOCUMENT_TYPE_1}}, {{DOCUMENT_TYPE_2}}, or {{DOCUMENT_TYPE_3}}), extract data via OCR, capture a live {{VERIFICATION_DATA}}, compare the {{VERIFICATION_DATA}} against the document photo, and enroll the {{SENSITIVE_DATA_TYPE}} template for future use. This is the most complex interaction with multiple validation checkpoints.

### Actors

- **Primary:** End User (new individual completing onboarding)
- **Secondary:** Document Processing Service, {{VERIFICATION_TYPE}} Enrollment Service, {{SECURITY_FEATURE}} Detection Engine

### Preconditions

- The user has a valid government-issued identity document
- The user's device supports {{VERIFICATION_DEVICE}} and (optionally) {{TECHNICAL_FEATURE}} for chip reading
- The onboarding workflow is configured for the user's jurisdiction

### Postconditions

- The user's identity is verified and a {{SENSITIVE_DATA_TYPE}} reference template is stored
- Document data is extracted and stored in the user profile
- An audit trail entry is created for regulatory compliance

### Diagram

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    classDef actor fill:#d4edda,stroke:#28a745,color:#000
    classDef system fill:#cce5ff,stroke:#0d6efd,color:#000
    classDef decision fill:#fff3cd,stroke:#ffc107,color:#000
    classDef terminal fill:#e2e3e5,stroke:#6c757d,color:#000

    Start([User begins onboarding flow]):::actor
    SelectDoc[User selects document type]:::actor
    ScanFront[System captures document front side]:::system
    ScanBack[System captures document back side]:::system
    OCR[System extracts data via OCR]:::system
    DocValid{Document data valid and not expired?}:::decision
    NFC{{{TECHNICAL_FEATURE}} chip available?}:::decision
    ReadChip[System reads {{TECHNICAL_FEATURE}} chip data]:::system
    CaptureSelfie[System captures live {{VERIFICATION_DATA}}]:::system
    LiveCheck{{{PRIMARY_VERIFICATION_METHOD}} passed?}:::decision
    FaceCompare{{{VERIFICATION_DATA}} matches document photo?}:::decision
    FraudCheck{{{SECURITY_FEATURE}} detection passed?}:::decision
    Enroll[System enrolls {{SENSITIVE_DATA_TYPE}} template]:::system
    CreateProfile[System creates verified user profile]:::system
    AuditLog[System writes compliance audit entry]:::system
    Success([Onboarding complete - account verified]):::terminal
    DocReject[System rejects document with reason]:::system
    LiveReject[System requests new {{VERIFICATION_DATA}} capture]:::system
    FaceReject[System flags mismatch for review]:::system
    FraudReject[System escalates to manual review]:::system
    Failure([User directed to support channel]):::terminal

    subgraph DocumentService["System Boundary: Document Processing"]
        ScanFront --> ScanBack
        ScanBack --> OCR
        OCR --> DocValid
    end

    subgraph BiometricService["System Boundary: {{VERIFICATION_TYPE}} Enrollment"]
        CaptureSelfie --> LiveCheck
        LiveCheck -->|Yes| FaceCompare
        FaceCompare -->|Yes| FraudCheck
        FraudCheck -->|Yes| Enroll
    end

    Start --> SelectDoc
    SelectDoc --> ScanFront
    DocValid -->|Yes| NFC
    DocValid -->|No| DocReject
    NFC -->|Yes| ReadChip
    NFC -->|No| CaptureSelfie
    ReadChip --> CaptureSelfie
    LiveCheck -->|No| LiveReject
    FaceCompare -->|No| FaceReject
    FraudCheck -->|No| FraudReject
    Enroll --> CreateProfile
    CreateProfile --> AuditLog
    AuditLog --> Success
    DocReject --> Failure
    LiveReject --> Failure
    FaceReject --> Failure
    FraudReject --> Failure
```

