## UC-3: Compliance Audit Trail Review

### Description

A compliance officer reviews the platform's audit trail to verify that all identity verification transactions comply with regulatory requirements. The officer queries verification records by date range, jurisdiction, or outcome status, inspects individual transaction details including consent records and data retention policies, and generates a compliance report suitable for submission to regulatory authorities.

### Actors

- **Primary:** Compliance Officer (internal reviewer with audit permissions)
- **Secondary:** Audit Service, Report Generation Engine

### Preconditions

- The compliance officer has authenticated with appropriate admin privileges
- Verification transactions exist within the queried time period
- The audit log service is accessible and data integrity is confirmed

### Postconditions

- The compliance officer has reviewed the requested audit records
- A compliance report is generated with findings and attestation status
- Any flagged non-compliant transactions are escalated for remediation

### Diagram

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    classDef actor fill:#d4edda,stroke:#28a745,color:#000
    classDef system fill:#cce5ff,stroke:#0d6efd,color:#000
    classDef decision fill:#fff3cd,stroke:#ffc107,color:#000
    classDef terminal fill:#e2e3e5,stroke:#6c757d,color:#000

    Start([Compliance officer opens audit console]):::actor
    SetFilters[Officer sets date range and filters]:::actor
    QueryLogs[System queries audit log database]:::system
    DisplayResults[System displays transaction summary]:::system
    SelectRecord[Officer selects transaction for detail view]:::actor
    ShowDetail[System shows full transaction detail]:::system
    CheckConsent{Consent record present and valid?}:::decision
    CheckRetention{Data retention policy followed?}:::decision
    FlagIssue[System flags non-compliant transaction]:::system
    MarkCompliant[System marks transaction as reviewed]:::system
    MoreRecords{More records to review?}:::decision
    GenerateReport[System generates compliance report]:::system
    ExportReport([Officer exports and signs report]):::terminal
    Escalate[System creates remediation ticket]:::system
    EscalateEnd([Issue escalated to data protection team]):::terminal

    subgraph AuditService["System Boundary: Audit Service"]
        QueryLogs --> DisplayResults
        ShowDetail --> CheckConsent
        CheckConsent -->|Yes| CheckRetention
        CheckRetention -->|Yes| MarkCompliant
        CheckConsent -->|No| FlagIssue
        CheckRetention -->|No| FlagIssue
    end

    Start --> SetFilters
    SetFilters --> QueryLogs
    DisplayResults --> SelectRecord
    SelectRecord --> ShowDetail
    MarkCompliant --> MoreRecords
    FlagIssue --> Escalate
    Escalate --> EscalateEnd
    MoreRecords -->|Yes| SelectRecord
    MoreRecords -->|No| GenerateReport
    GenerateReport --> ExportReport
```

